childPosts.alt: Photo by Kiran More on May 28, 2025. May be a graphic of text that says 'What's the point of losing your individuality... just for social media?'.
Photo by Kiran More on May 28, 2025. May be a meme of wagon and text that says 'A trend goes viral. Suddenly, everyone jumps on the bandwagon. But... for what?'.
Photo by Kiran More on May 28, 2025. May be a Twitter screenshot of text that says 'More followers? More likes? More engagement? More views?'.
Photo by Kiran More on May 28, 2025. May be an image of text that says 'And then what? Does it actually lead to something meaningful? Let me be honest with you... Not really.'.
Photo by Kiran More on May 28, 2025. May be an image of text that says 'I've had 5 reels cross 1 million views. Sounds exciling, right? Let me tell you what really happens.'.
Photo by Kiran More on May 28, 2025. May be an image of text that says 'Too many comments, hate, DM's, noise. You can't keep up... It drains you. Mentally. Quietly. Quickly.'.
Photo by Kiran More on May 28, 2025. May be an image of text that says 'And here's the kicker- Not a single brand reached out because a reel went went viral.'.

Photo by Kiran More on May 28, 2025. May be a graphic of text that says '"Viral" means your content pleased the masses. But as a creator, yu know deep down: Your Your content was never meant for the masses.'.

Photo by Kiran More on May 28, 2025. May be a graphic of text that says 'Brands reach out when they see alignment- between their vision and your personality- Not because you make cringe content that goes viral... but quality.'.
Photo by Kiran More on May 28, 2025. May be an image of text that says 'So stay true to your voice. Chase meaning, not metrics. Individuality Virality -Always.'.
